&lt;p&gt;As a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;112&quot; data-end=&quot;141&quot;&gt;Database Administrator (PostgreSQL DBA) I,&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;you’ll work as part of a collaborative and high-performing team providing your expertise to deliver technical solutions within the highest levels of the federal government by providing PostgreSQL expertise supporting highly visible, mission-critical applications; taking deep technical ownership of database platforms; executing disciplined operational practices; and maintaining database stability, performance, and security under constant operational demand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We know that you can’t have great &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.metrostar.com/&quot;&gt;technology services&lt;/a&gt; without amazing people. At MetroStar, we are &lt;strong&gt;obsessed &lt;/strong&gt;with&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;our people and have led a two-decade legacy of building the best and brightest teams. Because we know our future relies on our deep understanding and relentless focus on our people, we live by our mission: A passion for our people. Value for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, administer, and optimize databases in on-premises and cloud environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform database performance tuning, backups, replication, and recovery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce access controls, auditing, governance, and retention policies.&lt;br&gt;Manage schemas, indexes, stored procedures, and permissions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Kubernetes clusters and support containerized database and application operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer CI/CD pipelines and automation supporting database and application delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in Agile ceremonies and collaborative delivery activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support production operations with urgency and operational discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate technical risks, issues, and recommendations clearly to stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong customer trust through technical expertise, responsiveness, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll need to succeed:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Top Secret security clearance (current or previously held SCI access is preferable).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science or a related field is preferred; relevant experience may substitute.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certification meeting DoD 8140 (e.g., Security+, GSEC, or higher).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience as a database administrator or engineer with a primary focus on PostgreSQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing, implementing, managing, and tuning PostgreSQL databases in enterprise environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience owning high availability and disaster recovery configurations for PostgreSQL environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience enforcing database security controls, including encryption, key management, and compliance-aligned auditing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to own core PostgreSQL responsibilities on day one and ramp quickly on program-specific tooling in a fast-paced, mission-critical environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position is designated as essential personnel supporting continuity of operations and may require work during government shutdowns, emergencies, or other critical situations.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SALARY RANGE: $135,000 - $157,000&lt;/p&gt;
